WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.044 --> 00:00:04.046
[applause]

2
00:00:06.465 --> 00:00:10.469
[melancholic instrumental music playing]

3
00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:18.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

4
00:00:52.970 --> 00:00:56.639
[Eleanor] <i>I don't know if Robert
even remembers it by now</i>

5
00:00:56.640 --> 00:00:59.184
<i>but I met him first.</i>

6
00:00:59.935 --> 00:01:01.811
<i>That night. all those years ago.</i>

7
00:01:01.812 --> 00:01:06.024
<i>leaning against the kitchen cabinets.
wasted on cheap beer…</i>

8
00:01:07.317 --> 00:01:08.569
<i>I made him laugh</i>

9
00:01:09.152 --> 00:01:13.866
<i>and it was so spontaneous and natural.</i>

10
00:01:15.617 --> 00:01:17.202
<i>I knew he felt it too.</i>

11
00:01:18.495 --> 00:01:21.665
<i>But then she walked over.
and I introduced them.</i>

12
00:01:22.291 --> 00:01:24.625
<i>"Robert. this is Nancy."</i>

13
00:01:24.626 --> 00:01:28.297
[discordant notes playing]

14
00:01:29.965 --> 00:01:31.967
[phone buzzes]

15
00:01:40.976 --> 00:01:42.269
What is it?

16
00:01:46.648 --> 00:01:48.025
Oh. my God.

17
00:02:42.454 --> 00:02:45.289
[Eleanor] It doesn't even look like her.
[inhales deeply]

18
00:02:45.290 --> 00:02:48.794
It's Nancy obviously.
but it doesn't look like her.

19
00:02:50.963 --> 00:02:53.130
I defended Davide.

20
00:02:53.131 --> 00:02:56.301
I really thought
this didn't make any sense.

21
00:02:58.011 --> 00:02:59.012
It doesn't.

22
00:02:59.638 --> 00:03:01.556
[smacks lips]
Everyone gets to see this now

23
00:03:01.557 --> 00:03:04.141
and think whatever they want
before I've even had a chance to…

24
00:03:04.142 --> 00:03:07.020
- [sighs deeply]
- I know. but…

25
00:03:07.980 --> 00:03:13.735
I hope you know that whatever it is
that you are feeling. you can tell me.

26
00:03:15.529 --> 00:03:16.613
I mean. it's…

27
00:03:19.658 --> 00:03:21.951
bad enough to imagine her
with someone else.

28
00:03:21.952 --> 00:03:23.328
but seeing that…

29
00:03:25.747 --> 00:03:29.751
[sighs] I-I-I thought that when they had
the guy in custody. there'd…

30
00:03:31.545 --> 00:03:35.716
be some sense of relief.

31
00:03:40.762 --> 00:03:41.763
There's none.

32
00:03:43.515 --> 00:03:45.142
[stammers] Do you feel any?

33
00:03:47.102 --> 00:03:49.271
No. Not really.

34
00:03:50.189 --> 00:03:54.359
Despite all that… I still love her.

35
00:03:57.404 --> 00:03:59.573
I'd give anything to get her back.

36
00:04:01.200 --> 00:04:02.284
Is that crazy or…

37
00:04:03.785 --> 00:04:04.786
No.

38
00:04:07.497 --> 00:04:08.999
No. it's not crazy.

39
00:04:16.089 --> 00:04:17.591
This is me.

40
00:04:22.554 --> 00:04:23.847
- Hey.
- Yes?

41
00:04:27.226 --> 00:04:29.770
Thank you for coming with me today.

42
00:04:30.604 --> 00:04:34.024
It was nice being
somewhere important to her.

43
00:04:34.775 --> 00:04:36.777
Even if it was just for a little bit.

44
00:04:48.080 --> 00:04:49.540
- [Eleanor] Thank you.
- [driver] Thank you.

45
00:04:55.712 --> 00:04:58.131
Oh. shit. [sighs]

46
00:04:58.757 --> 00:04:59.758
Hey.

47
00:05:01.885 --> 00:05:07.849
Well. I came to confront you
about leaving me on "read." but… wow.

48
00:05:07.850 --> 00:05:09.350
I'm sorry.

49
00:05:09.351 --> 00:05:11.519
You know. if you had other plans.
you could've just told me.

50
00:05:11.520 --> 00:05:14.272
I had previous plans to go
to the ballet with a friend.

51
00:05:14.273 --> 00:05:16.566
and I'm… I… My phone was on silent.

52
00:05:16.567 --> 00:05:18.694
You know. it feels like
you don't take me seriously.

53
00:05:19.444 --> 00:05:23.531
I thought we both understood
that I'm not interested in serious. J.

54
00:05:23.532 --> 00:05:25.116
That's not what I meant.

55
00:05:25.117 --> 00:05:28.828
What I meant is you don't respect me.
like. as a person.

56
00:05:28.829 --> 00:05:29.913
I do.

57
00:05:30.539 --> 00:05:33.249
J. this is not an easy time
for me right now.

58
00:05:33.250 --> 00:05:35.877
It's not really even
about tonight. though. right?

59
00:05:35.878 --> 00:05:37.879
I mean. after
the St. Patrick's Day party. you…

60
00:05:37.880 --> 00:05:40.131
you come over two hours
after you said you would.

61
00:05:40.132 --> 00:05:41.299
The night your friend died.

62
00:05:41.300 --> 00:05:43.634
I mean. you text me at 9:00 p.m..
you show up at 1:00.

63
00:05:43.635 --> 00:05:46.470
- What is that about?
- No. it was just after 10:00.

64
00:05:46.471 --> 00:05:48.639
- No. it was definitely later than that.
- No. it wasn't.

65
00:05:48.640 --> 00:05:50.392
El. I stayed up.

66
00:05:52.811 --> 00:05:55.271
We should not be talking
about this in the street.

67
00:05:55.272 --> 00:05:57.107
I think we should go upstairs.

68
00:05:57.816 --> 00:06:00.109
I think we should open a bottle of wine

69
00:06:00.110 --> 00:06:03.113
and maybe try to talk
about this like adults.

70
00:06:04.198 --> 00:06:06.365
- Yeah?
- You said wine.

71
00:06:06.366 --> 00:06:09.368
Oh. it's the wine that got you.
not the adult part.

72
00:06:09.369 --> 00:06:10.953
[both chuckle]

73
00:06:10.954 --> 00:06:13.957
[dark hypnotic music playing]

74
00:07:01.630 --> 00:07:03.632
["Crazy" playing]

75
00:07:33.078 --> 00:07:34.079
[J] Morning.

76
00:07:34.788 --> 00:07:37.248
- Hey.
- No milk. No sugar.

77
00:07:37.249 --> 00:07:39.584
Just coffee grounds and hot water.

78
00:07:39.585 --> 00:07:41.085
- Your favorite.
- Thank you.

79
00:07:41.086 --> 00:07:42.462
- Yeah. [chuckles]
- [chuckles]

80
00:07:43.547 --> 00:07:44.922
You're gonna be late for work.

81
00:07:44.923 --> 00:07:46.842
You know. I think my boss will understand.

82
00:07:47.968 --> 00:07:50.052
- Oh. wow. [chuckles]
- [chuckles]

83
00:07:50.053 --> 00:07:52.805
You know. I-I didn't know
you were into fishing. Are you?

84
00:07:52.806 --> 00:07:53.891
I'm not.

85
00:07:55.767 --> 00:07:59.770
Okay. well. you know. if you wanna learn.
I know this great spot at Lake Gregory--

86
00:07:59.771 --> 00:08:02.315
J. you should really get to the office.

87
00:08:02.316 --> 00:08:05.484
Yeah. No. I… I-I should. [chuckles]

88
00:08:05.485 --> 00:08:08.404
Let me do that. I'll… I'll see you there.

89
00:08:08.405 --> 00:08:09.406
Yeah.

90
00:08:12.576 --> 00:08:13.702
[door closes]

91
00:08:18.415 --> 00:08:20.417
[whistling]

92
00:08:22.044 --> 00:08:24.921
- [child 1] I call chocolate.
- [child 2] I wanted the chocolate one.

93
00:08:24.922 --> 00:08:26.088
[child 1] Too bad. I called dibs.

94
00:08:26.089 --> 00:08:28.675
[Eleanor] I'm sorry. sweetheart.
I have to honor the dibs.

95
00:08:29.259 --> 00:08:33.221
Backpacks on in 20 minutes. girls.
What do you say to Aunt Ellie?

96
00:08:33.222 --> 00:08:34.805
- [child 1] Thank you. Aunt Ellie.
- Welcome.

97
00:08:34.806 --> 00:08:36.516
- [child 2] Thank you.
- Is it too much sugar?

98
00:08:36.517 --> 00:08:38.392
- There's no such thing.
- [chuckles]

99
00:08:38.393 --> 00:08:39.726
I wish you were my mother. [chuckles]

100
00:08:39.727 --> 00:08:40.811
So. what were you gonna tell me

101
00:08:40.812 --> 00:08:42.187
- about the ballet?
- [Howard] That's it.

102
00:08:42.188 --> 00:08:44.273
Okay. so. what. I'm just not allowed
to use the car anymore?

103
00:08:44.274 --> 00:08:45.441
This is what happens. Marcus.

104
00:08:45.442 --> 00:08:47.944
When you sit in my car and vape in secret.
it's gonna keep doing this.

105
00:08:47.945 --> 00:08:49.028
- I wasn't vaping.
- Hey. guys.

106
00:08:49.029 --> 00:08:50.112
- Hey. El.
- [Howard] Eleanor.

107
00:08:50.113 --> 00:08:51.864
Hey. Mom. could you tell him
to cut me some slack?

108
00:08:51.865 --> 00:08:53.241
- I'm trying to ask for a jump.
- Sweetie.

109
00:08:53.242 --> 00:08:55.576
- Why don't you go outside with your dad?
- Let's find the jumper cables.

110
00:08:55.577 --> 00:08:57.995
- I am so sorry about all of this.
- No. it's okay.

111
00:08:57.996 --> 00:09:00.039
I promise. you will have
my full attention.

112
00:09:00.040 --> 00:09:01.958
- I'm just gonna…
- Let me just make some room.

113
00:09:01.959 --> 00:09:05.044
- Oh. God. I'm so sorry.
- Oh. no. no. that's okay. I'll get it.

114
00:09:05.045 --> 00:09:06.463
I'll get it. Ellie. let me get that…

115
00:09:11.134 --> 00:09:12.970
- What is this?
- It's nothing.

116
00:09:13.470 --> 00:09:15.514
Nothing? It's a police report.

117
00:09:17.432 --> 00:09:19.684
[sighs] They're public records.

118
00:09:19.685 --> 00:09:21.727
Yes. but why do you have them?

119
00:09:21.728 --> 00:09:24.647
Because something doesn't feel right.

120
00:09:24.648 --> 00:09:26.274
I know Davide was arrested.

121
00:09:26.275 --> 00:09:28.776
but he was arrested for robbery.
not murder.

122
00:09:28.777 --> 00:09:32.071
because of some
random informant's testimony.

123
00:09:32.072 --> 00:09:33.781
I mean. come on. it's sketchy.

124
00:09:33.782 --> 00:09:37.785
The news is trying to connect it to Nancy.
and it's not.

125
00:09:37.786 --> 00:09:40.997
So. you're investing
a lot of time on this.

126
00:09:40.998 --> 00:09:45.084
Oh. don't do that.
Don't make me sound like I'm fragile.

127
00:09:45.085 --> 00:09:46.210
[chuckles]

128
00:09:46.211 --> 00:09:48.087
I get enough of that around here.

129
00:09:48.088 --> 00:09:49.089
Okay.

130
00:10:00.475 --> 00:10:02.059
Oh. thank you.

131
00:10:02.060 --> 00:10:04.229
I just couldn't get myself to do it.

132
00:10:05.480 --> 00:10:06.856
I get it.

133
00:10:06.857 --> 00:10:10.735
I keep staring at old text messages
from her that I can't delete.

134
00:10:10.736 --> 00:10:12.987
- Yeah.
- [inhales deeply]

135
00:10:12.988 --> 00:10:16.365
- Was this your breakfast?
- I haven't had much of an appetite.

136
00:10:16.366 --> 00:10:18.202
- [sighs]
- Something else going on?

137
00:10:18.952 --> 00:10:23.122
Uh. i-it's just I don't wanna bother you
with it on top of everything else.

138
00:10:23.123 --> 00:10:24.124
What is it?

139
00:10:26.877 --> 00:10:31.297
Kit asked me today what I'm doing
for Cora's birthday this weekend.

140
00:10:31.298 --> 00:10:33.090
- Oh.
- I totally forgot about it.

141
00:10:33.091 --> 00:10:35.927
So now I'm trying to figure out this DJ
for some silent disco

142
00:10:35.928 --> 00:10:37.720
that I have no idea if she's even into.

143
00:10:37.721 --> 00:10:40.890
and I'm googling
"17-year-old girl birthday party."

144
00:10:40.891 --> 00:10:43.644
Careful. You don't wanna end up on a list.

145
00:10:44.353 --> 00:10:47.188
Thanks. Now. I feel like
an idiot and a pervert.

146
00:10:47.189 --> 00:10:49.107
- [laughs]
- [chuckles]

147
00:10:50.192 --> 00:10:53.861
[sighs] What kind of father forgets
his own daughter's birthday?

148
00:10:53.862 --> 00:10:55.613
Oh. I can't believe it.

149
00:10:55.614 --> 00:10:57.865
- One married to Nancy.
- Yeah.

150
00:10:57.866 --> 00:10:59.825
You've never had to
think about any of this.

151
00:10:59.826 --> 00:11:01.869
Yeah. but I wanna at least try. you know?

152
00:11:01.870 --> 00:11:04.706
It's her first birthday after…

153
00:11:08.752 --> 00:11:10.753
Nancy always made them magical.

154
00:11:10.754 --> 00:11:13.047
[Nancy] <i>I'm not gonna
give a speech. I swear.</i>

155
00:11:13.048 --> 00:11:16.884
Um. 16 years ago.
the greatest gift came into my life.

156
00:11:16.885 --> 00:11:20.096
and today. we get to celebrate her.

157
00:11:20.097 --> 00:11:23.599
So. without further ado.
the birthday girl.

158
00:11:23.600 --> 00:11:26.478
- My baby girl Cora.
- [guests cheering]

159
00:11:28.438 --> 00:11:29.897
Have fun tonight.

160
00:11:29.898 --> 00:11:32.609
["Birthday Girl" playing]

161
00:11:42.828 --> 00:11:44.288
[laughs]

162
00:11:47.791 --> 00:11:51.170
[sinister music playing]

163
00:11:56.884 --> 00:11:58.552
[Robert] I just don't wanna fuck it up.

164
00:12:00.179 --> 00:12:01.888
I could help.

165
00:12:01.889 --> 00:12:05.641
I mean. I've been to my fair share
of Nancy festivities.

166
00:12:05.642 --> 00:12:08.436
I think I could try to figure it out.

167
00:12:08.437 --> 00:12:11.772
- It's not too much?
- It's Cora. What's too much?

168
00:12:11.773 --> 00:12:14.942
- There is no too much.
- Oh. [exhales deeply] Thank you.

169
00:12:14.943 --> 00:12:17.028
Yeah. Yeah. Okay.

170
00:12:17.029 --> 00:12:19.865
- Just send me what you have so far. okay?
- Uh… Yeah. Okay.

171
00:12:21.867 --> 00:12:23.368
- [sighs]
- [door closes]

172
00:12:26.330 --> 00:12:29.833
Detective Ganz. are you looking
to buy in this neighborhood?

173
00:12:30.417 --> 00:12:32.835
Not with what they pay me. sadly.

174
00:12:32.836 --> 00:12:34.671
[chuckles] She's beautiful.

175
00:12:35.297 --> 00:12:37.382
- Thank you.
- Incredible lines.

176
00:12:38.008 --> 00:12:42.095
Not many people would custom paint
a vintage 450 SL. though.

177
00:12:42.721 --> 00:12:45.515
Then again. if money is no object.
what does it matter

178
00:12:45.516 --> 00:12:48.644
if you devalue a classic
in mint condition?

179
00:12:50.270 --> 00:12:52.272
- To each his own.
- Yeah.

180
00:12:52.981 --> 00:12:53.982
Have a good day.

181
00:12:54.566 --> 00:12:56.692
Actually. if you don't mind. uh…

182
00:12:56.693 --> 00:12:57.736
[clears throat]

183
00:12:58.445 --> 00:13:00.029
I'm sure you've seen this picture.

184
00:13:00.030 --> 00:13:04.659
- Yeah. it's all over the news.
- Yeah. I have studied this picture a lot.

185
00:13:04.660 --> 00:13:10.582
and what I can't get over is the…
the look on Mrs. Hennessey's face.

186
00:13:11.542 --> 00:13:15.878
Right? She looks relaxed.
not a bit out of place.

187
00:13:15.879 --> 00:13:17.380
But it doesn't track.

188
00:13:17.381 --> 00:13:21.843
What does a Pasadena socialite
have in common with this crowd?

189
00:13:21.844 --> 00:13:24.263
She wasn't always a socialite.

190
00:13:25.055 --> 00:13:26.848
She had a life before Robert.

191
00:13:26.849 --> 00:13:28.267
What kind of life?

192
00:13:29.059 --> 00:13:30.351
[Eleanor] A tough one.

193
00:13:30.352 --> 00:13:34.272
Alcoholic mother. abusive stepfather.
trailer park.

194
00:13:34.273 --> 00:13:36.358
It was not easy.

195
00:13:36.859 --> 00:13:39.695
Yeah. yeah.
No. we looked into her history.

196
00:13:40.737 --> 00:13:42.613
That kinda makes this even more peculiar.

197
00:13:42.614 --> 00:13:45.199
- Why?
- Well. a woman like that.

198
00:13:45.200 --> 00:13:49.204
what does she have in common
with Robert and his family?

199
00:13:50.581 --> 00:13:51.915
Or with you?

200
00:13:52.708 --> 00:13:55.960
Is my friendship under investigation?

201
00:13:55.961 --> 00:13:58.380
No. It is not.

202
00:13:59.089 --> 00:14:01.383
Is the robbery charge just bullshit?

203
00:14:02.092 --> 00:14:03.676
I feel like you wouldn't be
asking me all this

204
00:14:03.677 --> 00:14:05.721
if you had a real case against Davide.

205
00:14:06.388 --> 00:14:08.390
Are you looking into someone else?

206
00:14:10.767 --> 00:14:12.186
Thank you for your time.

207
00:14:21.195 --> 00:14:23.947
[slow tense music playing]

208
00:14:44.384 --> 00:14:47.679
- [horns honking]
- [tires screeching]

209
00:14:50.182 --> 00:14:52.351
- Shit.
- Roll down your window!

210
00:14:55.562 --> 00:14:58.481
You have no right to be following me.
This is harassment.

211
00:14:58.482 --> 00:15:01.234
I want your name and your badge number.

212
00:15:01.235 --> 00:15:02.236
[chuckles] I'm not a cop.

213
00:15:03.237 --> 00:15:04.821
I work for Donovan.

214
00:15:06.406 --> 00:15:10.244
[chuckling] Okay.

215
00:15:12.913 --> 00:15:14.998
[Donovan] Have you ever been
to a war zone?

216
00:15:15.624 --> 00:15:18.084
The loss of life. it changes you.

217
00:15:18.085 --> 00:15:20.711
So. I had them apply for asylum.

218
00:15:20.712 --> 00:15:24.132
pulled some of those governmental strings
we talked about. and…

219
00:15:24.716 --> 00:15:29.262
Long story short. they now have
a thriving dental practice.

220
00:15:29.263 --> 00:15:32.807
Their daughter just graduated
from Vassar last year.

221
00:15:32.808 --> 00:15:34.059
That's incredible.

222
00:15:35.269 --> 00:15:39.273
Well. when your heart is speaking to you.
you ought to listen.

223
00:15:40.190 --> 00:15:43.776
Ladies. if you'll excuse me.
I have just a little business to tend to.

224
00:15:43.777 --> 00:15:45.779
but I'll see you at the pool
a little later.

225
00:15:47.030 --> 00:15:48.073
[chuckles]

226
00:15:49.199 --> 00:15:52.619
That's cute. You use my stories
to pick up women?

227
00:15:53.245 --> 00:15:54.329
It's a good story.

228
00:15:55.038 --> 00:15:57.456
And Mom and I do
fund your little charity thing.

229
00:15:57.457 --> 00:15:59.041
so it's also my story.

230
00:15:59.042 --> 00:16:02.837
- "Little charity thing"? Thanks. Donnie.
- [chuckles]

231
00:16:02.838 --> 00:16:05.256
The daughter went to Ohio State.
by the way.

232
00:16:05.257 --> 00:16:06.424
Vassar sounded better.

233
00:16:06.425 --> 00:16:10.428
- Wow. [chuckles]
- So. my guy Winston said you can sprint.

234
00:16:10.429 --> 00:16:12.346
Yeah. when I'm compelled to.

235
00:16:12.347 --> 00:16:15.308
In some families.
when somebody's friend dies.

236
00:16:15.309 --> 00:16:18.645
they buy them flowers or a basket
or even offer a hug.

237
00:16:19.396 --> 00:16:20.522
Can't relate.

238
00:16:21.190 --> 00:16:24.066
They say it's the curse
of the well-bred and the wealthy.

239
00:16:24.067 --> 00:16:26.152
- [chuckles] Okay.
- Not enough hugs.

240
00:16:26.153 --> 00:16:27.987
Too much emotional sublimation. you know?

241
00:16:27.988 --> 00:16:31.282
Right. Since your man Winston
is done stalking me.

242
00:16:31.283 --> 00:16:34.203
and you can see
that I'm very safe. very sound.

243
00:16:34.870 --> 00:16:36.413
maybe you guys go home.

244
00:16:38.457 --> 00:16:40.500
- I would love to.
- Mm-hmm.

245
00:16:40.501 --> 00:16:42.168
I have better things
to do than babysit you.

246
00:16:42.169 --> 00:16:44.337
- But…
- But when tragedy strikes.

247
00:16:44.338 --> 00:16:46.798
you do have a tendency
to get unpredictable.

248
00:16:47.591 --> 00:16:49.383
- That's not fair.
- No?

249
00:16:49.384 --> 00:16:50.468
No.

250
00:16:50.469 --> 00:16:52.553
- When Dad died--
- Don't… No… Don't do that.

251
00:16:52.554 --> 00:16:54.764
Do not bring him into this.

252
00:16:54.765 --> 00:16:57.601
I was in a very different place back then.

253
00:16:59.853 --> 00:17:01.145
Seriously?

254
00:17:01.146 --> 00:17:03.564
If I had confronted you without evidence.
you would have denied it.

255
00:17:03.565 --> 00:17:05.650
This is two old friends grieving.

256
00:17:05.651 --> 00:17:06.901
Those look like pretty big smiles

257
00:17:06.902 --> 00:17:09.444
- for grieving.
- We are honoring the passion

258
00:17:09.445 --> 00:17:10.864
of somebody we loved.

259
00:17:12.406 --> 00:17:15.827
E. you and I both know
you love to fix a broken toy.

260
00:17:16.494 --> 00:17:18.412
Especially a certain nice Caucasian one.

261
00:17:18.413 --> 00:17:20.748
- Maybe if you'd joined the BSU…
- What?

262
00:17:20.749 --> 00:17:22.415
- …or some Black sorority…
- Oh. here we go.

263
00:17:22.416 --> 00:17:23.793
…you'd be with a Jamal or a Terrell

264
00:17:23.794 --> 00:17:26.379
- instead of stuck on you-know-who.
- I cannot.

265
00:17:26.380 --> 00:17:28.005
You're an ass.

266
00:17:28.006 --> 00:17:32.176
Why don't you just admit that you have
a blind spot when it comes to Robert?

267
00:17:32.177 --> 00:17:33.637
And you always have.

268
00:17:35.222 --> 00:17:36.223
Are you done?

269
00:17:36.807 --> 00:17:38.809
- [stammers]
- Stop fucking following me.

270
00:17:56.827 --> 00:17:57.828
[phone chimes]

271
00:18:08.922 --> 00:18:10.215
[siren wails]

272
00:18:19.183 --> 00:18:21.602
[chattering on radio]

273
00:18:47.878 --> 00:18:48.879
They had a warrant.

274
00:18:49.796 --> 00:18:51.965
A warrant for what?

275
00:18:52.758 --> 00:18:54.300
[Robert] Some of Nancy's things.

276
00:18:54.301 --> 00:18:55.885
Our financial records.

277
00:18:55.886 --> 00:18:59.389
They wanted to see if I stood to gain
anything from having my wife killed.

278
00:19:00.098 --> 00:19:01.349
Oh. my God.

279
00:19:01.350 --> 00:19:03.060
[Robert] And they took my laptop.

280
00:19:03.644 --> 00:19:05.811
I was gonna call Kit.
but she would've called my father.

281
00:19:05.812 --> 00:19:08.148
and he would've turned this
into a whole shitstorm.

282
00:19:10.400 --> 00:19:12.527
I think they're just doing
their due diligence. Robert.

283
00:19:12.528 --> 00:19:14.779
- They're not gonna find anything.
- Of course not.

284
00:19:14.780 --> 00:19:17.281
I didn't… I wasn't implying that…
I was saying that--

285
00:19:17.282 --> 00:19:18.449
You're right. I'm sorry.

286
00:19:18.450 --> 00:19:20.536
I just… This whole thing is just…

287
00:19:22.955 --> 00:19:26.250
Maybe this isn't the best time
to throw a birthday party.

288
00:19:29.378 --> 00:19:31.213
I disagree. [chuckles]

289
00:19:32.172 --> 00:19:35.175
I think we have to keep on living.
you know?

290
00:19:35.968 --> 00:19:37.761
Cora deserves some normalcy.

291
00:19:38.679 --> 00:19:39.763
As do you.

292
00:19:41.390 --> 00:19:43.392
And I think
it's what Nancy would've wanted.

293
00:19:52.943 --> 00:19:56.946
[J] So. if we are gonna add
someone to the team in Liberia.

294
00:19:56.947 --> 00:19:58.699
my vote would be Chelsea.

295
00:19:59.449 --> 00:20:01.284
- Has she volunteered?
- [phone chimes]

296
00:20:01.285 --> 00:20:04.078
{\an8}[J] Uh. no.
but she's shown some initiative.

297
00:20:04.079 --> 00:20:06.582
{\an8}She has great local connections
I think might help us.

298
00:20:09.960 --> 00:20:12.379
El… El.

299
00:20:13.797 --> 00:20:15.381
Uh. yes. I'm sorry.

300
00:20:15.382 --> 00:20:16.924
Yeah. No. it's all good.

301
00:20:16.925 --> 00:20:19.427
Um. I can reach out to her. though.
if you'd like me to.

302
00:20:19.428 --> 00:20:20.429
Sure.

303
00:20:21.013 --> 00:20:23.472
Um. hey. J.

304
00:20:23.473 --> 00:20:25.141
This isn't gonna happen.

305
00:20:25.142 --> 00:20:29.980
but the police investigation
is getting kinda complicated. so…

306
00:20:31.523 --> 00:20:35.818
if someone were to ask you about me…

307
00:20:35.819 --> 00:20:38.238
I know. I got it.

308
00:20:39.031 --> 00:20:40.531
I won't say anything. okay?

309
00:20:40.532 --> 00:20:41.700
No. you can.

310
00:20:42.618 --> 00:20:44.536
You can tell them
that I was at your place.

311
00:20:47.372 --> 00:20:48.415
[chuckles]

312
00:20:48.916 --> 00:20:51.000
- I thought we were being discreet.
- We are.

313
00:20:51.001 --> 00:20:55.630
But. you know. if somebody asks.
then we wanna be helpful.

314
00:20:55.631 --> 00:20:56.881
- Ellie.
- Yes?

315
00:20:56.882 --> 00:20:58.049
Do you have a second?

316
00:20:58.050 --> 00:20:59.134
Yes. of course.

317
00:20:59.885 --> 00:21:01.719
Can you give me a second? Sorry.

318
00:21:01.720 --> 00:21:03.222
- Oh. yeah. Of course.
- Thank you.

319
00:21:05.766 --> 00:21:07.141
What's up? You okay?

320
00:21:07.142 --> 00:21:08.143
It's my mom.

321
00:21:09.019 --> 00:21:10.937
Someone has to pick her up
from the police station.

322
00:21:10.938 --> 00:21:12.772
What? What do you mean?

323
00:21:12.773 --> 00:21:14.775
[tense music playing]

324
00:21:27.621 --> 00:21:29.664
I've contacted an attorney.
He's on his way.

325
00:21:29.665 --> 00:21:32.375
She is not going to answer any questions
until he gets here.

326
00:21:32.376 --> 00:21:33.668
We're not arresting her.

327
00:21:33.669 --> 00:21:36.128
I just need someone
to take her off our hands.

328
00:21:36.129 --> 00:21:37.505
I don't understand.

329
00:21:37.506 --> 00:21:41.300
I found out that your friend
has been harassing my officers.

330
00:21:41.301 --> 00:21:42.718
- What?
- Last week alone.

331
00:21:42.719 --> 00:21:46.889
she submitted 20 public records requests.

332
00:21:46.890 --> 00:21:48.850
and today she crossed a line.

333
00:21:48.851 --> 00:21:50.853
Next time. handcuffs.

334
00:21:57.192 --> 00:21:59.569
- What the hell did you do?
- Doesn't matter.

335
00:21:59.570 --> 00:22:01.738
No. actually it matters a lot.

336
00:22:03.198 --> 00:22:04.783
- I may have used the C-word.
- What?

337
00:22:05.534 --> 00:22:07.785
- While throwing a stapler.
- Oh. my God.

338
00:22:07.786 --> 00:22:09.370
- At a wall.
- Okay.

339
00:22:09.371 --> 00:22:11.081
- Not a person.
- Are you okay?

340
00:22:11.707 --> 00:22:14.542
Look. they wasted all of this time
on this Davide thing.

341
00:22:14.543 --> 00:22:17.879
And meanwhile.
they won't look at any of my leads.

342
00:22:17.880 --> 00:22:21.007
I circled every single David
in our college yearbooks.

343
00:22:21.008 --> 00:22:23.801
I found every David
that she follows on social media.

344
00:22:23.802 --> 00:22:27.221
I even found a William David
who owns a flower shop in Texas.

345
00:22:27.222 --> 00:22:29.932
and she liked his post on Pinterest.
and I just…

346
00:22:29.933 --> 00:22:31.350
I know it sounds crazy. but…

347
00:22:31.351 --> 00:22:33.478
- Do not be mad at me for asking this.
- What?

348
00:22:34.771 --> 00:22:36.189
Are you taking the…

349
00:22:36.190 --> 00:22:37.565
No. El. come on.

350
00:22:37.566 --> 00:22:40.651
I haven't taken more
than an aspirin in six months. okay?

351
00:22:40.652 --> 00:22:41.653
[Eleanor] Okay.

352
00:22:43.447 --> 00:22:45.115
I'm sorry. I can't let this go.

353
00:22:46.992 --> 00:22:49.411
[stammers] But she told you. El.

354
00:22:50.537 --> 00:22:53.207
She shut me out.
and you got to hear things…

355
00:22:54.875 --> 00:22:56.043
And now I never will.

356
00:22:56.877 --> 00:22:58.211
She shut me out too.

357
00:22:58.212 --> 00:23:00.214
There's so much shit I don't know.

358
00:23:02.132 --> 00:23:05.177
I wish I could just distract myself
like you can.

359
00:23:06.887 --> 00:23:08.388
With work and Robert.

360
00:23:11.016 --> 00:23:15.394
I think tonight we should just have
a very relaxed evening. okay?

361
00:23:15.395 --> 00:23:16.479
I'm gonna get some takeout.

362
00:23:16.480 --> 00:23:18.564
I'm gonna bring it over for you
and the kids and Howard.

363
00:23:18.565 --> 00:23:21.067
We're just gonna… chillax.

364
00:23:21.068 --> 00:23:23.194
- Hmm. Okay.
- Okay? Okay.

365
00:23:23.195 --> 00:23:24.779
Didn't realize anyone said that anymore.

366
00:23:24.780 --> 00:23:26.197
[chuckles] I do.

367
00:23:26.198 --> 00:23:28.283
- We'll chillax.
- [chuckles]

368
00:23:30.452 --> 00:23:31.495
[grunts]

369
00:23:33.622 --> 00:23:34.873
[grunts]

370
00:23:35.666 --> 00:23:38.252
[grunting]

371
00:23:49.012 --> 00:23:51.098
- Hey. I just came to drop…
- [grunts]

372
00:23:51.682 --> 00:23:53.934
- Robert. Hey.
- [grunts]

373
00:23:55.102 --> 00:23:56.270
- [grunts]
- Robert!

374
00:23:56.770 --> 00:23:58.397
[grunts]

375
00:23:59.147 --> 00:24:01.358
- Hey.
- Hey.

376
00:24:02.067 --> 00:24:03.652
[Eleanor] That looked cathartic.

377
00:24:04.361 --> 00:24:05.529
Yeah. [stammers]

378
00:24:06.446 --> 00:24:10.366
Whenever I wanna drink. I come down here
and hit some balls instead.

379
00:24:10.367 --> 00:24:12.869
- How long have you been out here?
- Uh…

380
00:24:12.870 --> 00:24:14.246
[groans] Whoa.

381
00:24:14.872 --> 00:24:16.999
I guess I really wanted a drink.

382
00:24:17.583 --> 00:24:19.334
[sighs] Everything okay?

383
00:24:19.877 --> 00:24:21.335
Have you heard from the police?

384
00:24:21.336 --> 00:24:23.212
They dropped off a few of Nancy's boxes.

385
00:24:23.213 --> 00:24:24.506
but aside from that. nothing.

386
00:24:25.132 --> 00:24:27.217
Did hear from your brother. though.
[scoffs]

387
00:24:28.177 --> 00:24:29.595
- Are you joking?
- [chuckles]

388
00:24:30.512 --> 00:24:31.846
I was pretty shocked he called me.

389
00:24:31.847 --> 00:24:33.015
It's… It's been so many years.

390
00:24:33.599 --> 00:24:36.143
What… I don't… What did he want?

391
00:24:36.977 --> 00:24:39.270
- Offer his condolences.
- Right.

392
00:24:39.271 --> 00:24:42.190
- The guy never liked me.
- Oh. come on.

393
00:24:42.191 --> 00:24:43.859
Did… Did I ever tell
you what he said to me?

394
00:24:44.776 --> 00:24:46.861
- No.
- Oh. it was on that fishing trip

395
00:24:46.862 --> 00:24:49.155
with your dad.
Freshman year. Spring break.

396
00:24:49.156 --> 00:24:50.281
[Eleanor] Yeah.

397
00:24:50.282 --> 00:24:52.074
About an hour after we arrived.

398
00:24:52.075 --> 00:24:55.995
Donovan cornered me and told me
that you were strictly off-limits.

399
00:24:55.996 --> 00:24:57.372
Romantically speaking.

400
00:24:58.290 --> 00:25:00.082
Why would he do that? [chuckles]

401
00:25:00.083 --> 00:25:02.835
I'm sure he was just
doing the big-brother thing.

402
00:25:02.836 --> 00:25:04.254
I wouldn't hold it against him.

403
00:25:04.796 --> 00:25:06.506
I'm gonna. um. hop in the shower.

404
00:25:06.507 --> 00:25:07.508
Are you sticking around?

405
00:25:08.091 --> 00:25:09.718
- I'm not sure.
- Okay.

406
00:25:19.561 --> 00:25:22.189
[pop music playing on speakers]

407
00:25:24.775 --> 00:25:26.443
What decade do you think we're living in?

408
00:25:28.320 --> 00:25:30.613
I've been out in the sun a while.
You're gonna have to give me a second.

409
00:25:30.614 --> 00:25:32.031
Do you think this is the dark ages

410
00:25:32.032 --> 00:25:35.618
where you get to decide who I date.
and who I don't date?

411
00:25:35.619 --> 00:25:38.496
Because despite
what you and our mother believe.

412
00:25:38.497 --> 00:25:41.290
I am an adult. I'm an adult.

413
00:25:41.291 --> 00:25:43.960
I'm somebody who people look up to
and rely on.

414
00:25:43.961 --> 00:25:47.130
I make responsible decisions
about what I want and what I do.

415
00:25:48.257 --> 00:25:49.258
Okay.

416
00:25:50.259 --> 00:25:51.927
All right. why don't you have a seat?

417
00:25:52.469 --> 00:25:54.596
Tell me what
we're so worked up about today.

418
00:25:55.556 --> 00:25:56.640
You called Robert.

419
00:25:58.976 --> 00:26:01.144
That was fast. You two talk a lot. huh?

420
00:26:02.479 --> 00:26:06.440
He told me what you said
back then when you first met him.

421
00:26:06.441 --> 00:26:08.944
That you forbade him from dating me.

422
00:26:09.736 --> 00:26:11.154
That's a deep cut. [sighs]

423
00:26:11.989 --> 00:26:13.197
Do you wanna tell me why?

424
00:26:13.198 --> 00:26:14.365
Come on. E. We both know why.

425
00:26:14.366 --> 00:26:17.619
No. I really don't.
I think I might need to hear you say it.

426
00:26:18.203 --> 00:26:19.204
All right.

427
00:26:21.874 --> 00:26:22.875
I see it.

428
00:26:24.418 --> 00:26:29.255
You're both smart. sensitive.
like-minded people.

429
00:26:29.256 --> 00:26:33.677
In a vacuum.
if the rest of the world doesn't exist…

430
00:26:34.803 --> 00:26:38.098
you're the perfect interracial
Ken and Barbie.

431
00:26:39.224 --> 00:26:41.310
- But because the world doesn't--
- Not the world.

432
00:26:42.060 --> 00:26:44.478
- His family.
- No. you don't know anything

433
00:26:44.479 --> 00:26:47.356
- about his family.
- The Hennesseys are old money.

434
00:26:47.357 --> 00:26:49.066
bone-deep entitlement.

435
00:26:49.067 --> 00:26:53.613
They think. uh. accountability is a myth.
and ethics are a joke.

436
00:26:53.614 --> 00:26:56.200
Who do you think pulled the strings
to get Davide arrested?

437
00:26:56.992 --> 00:26:59.702
That is a classic
Hennessey move right there.

438
00:26:59.703 --> 00:27:01.787
Closing ranks to protect their own.

439
00:27:01.788 --> 00:27:04.458
No. You sound ridiculous right now.

440
00:27:05.000 --> 00:27:06.834
Robert did not kill Nancy.

441
00:27:06.835 --> 00:27:09.337
She had a lover. His name was David.

442
00:27:09.338 --> 00:27:10.922
and David killed her.

443
00:27:10.923 --> 00:27:14.383
- So maybe Robert found out about David.
- He didn't know about David.

444
00:27:14.384 --> 00:27:16.552
He didn't even know about the affair
until I told him.

445
00:27:16.553 --> 00:27:18.680
and by the time I told him.
Nancy was already dead.

446
00:27:19.473 --> 00:27:20.682
Wait a second. You…

447
00:27:22.935 --> 00:27:26.729
You told Robert
that his wife was stepping out on him?

448
00:27:26.730 --> 00:27:27.731
Yes.

449
00:27:28.524 --> 00:27:30.107
Because he was worried.

450
00:27:30.108 --> 00:27:32.401
He was gonna call the police.
and I wanted to help.

451
00:27:32.402 --> 00:27:36.240
It seems like all you do lately
is help Robert.

452
00:27:38.700 --> 00:27:40.535
You wanted to be his backup plan.

453
00:27:40.536 --> 00:27:44.455
You have no idea
what you are talking about.

454
00:27:44.456 --> 00:27:45.707
- Oh. no?
- No.

455
00:27:55.467 --> 00:27:57.553
[guests laughing]

456
00:27:58.637 --> 00:28:00.638
I can't believe Mommy went to jail.

457
00:28:00.639 --> 00:28:04.225
I didn't.
I was practicing civil disobedience.

458
00:28:04.226 --> 00:28:06.353
which we all have a right to do.

459
00:28:09.356 --> 00:28:11.357
But I'm sorry that I scared you guys.

460
00:28:11.358 --> 00:28:12.942
- I wasn't scared.
- Oh. okay.

461
00:28:12.943 --> 00:28:15.194
- Dad was.
- [chuckles]

462
00:28:15.195 --> 00:28:16.530
[chuckles]

463
00:28:19.032 --> 00:28:21.200
What? Hey. I'm still working on that.

464
00:28:21.201 --> 00:28:22.493
I think we're done here.

465
00:28:22.494 --> 00:28:24.370
That is. unless anyone
wants to help me clean up.

466
00:28:24.371 --> 00:28:25.496
- Not it!
- Not it.

467
00:28:25.497 --> 00:28:26.873
Hey. hey. No. no. no. H…

468
00:28:26.874 --> 00:28:28.375
Get… Junie. get back here.

469
00:28:28.917 --> 00:28:30.919
- I'll help. I'll help.
- Thank you.

470
00:28:32.629 --> 00:28:33.630
They were scared.

471
00:28:34.214 --> 00:28:36.257
They don't wanna say it. but they were.

472
00:28:36.258 --> 00:28:39.428
You just left with no explanation.
and then we get a call from the cops.

473
00:28:43.098 --> 00:28:44.516
I know she meant a lot to you.

474
00:28:45.392 --> 00:28:46.727
but so does your family.

475
00:28:48.604 --> 00:28:50.898
They… They're still here. They need you.

476
00:28:51.481 --> 00:28:53.567
- We need you.
- [stammers] I don't know how to…

477
00:28:54.109 --> 00:28:56.236
I don't know how to let it go. okay?

478
00:28:58.822 --> 00:29:02.242
Thank you. Eleanor.
for the help and the noodles.

479
00:29:03.827 --> 00:29:05.787
- No problem.
- [Howard clears throat]

480
00:29:07.748 --> 00:29:10.459
- [Mary huffs]
- [door opens. closes]

481
00:29:13.670 --> 00:29:15.005
[sighs]

482
00:29:17.799 --> 00:29:19.175
He has a right to be concerned.

483
00:29:19.176 --> 00:29:20.635
I know. I know.

484
00:29:20.636 --> 00:29:24.932
Um. okay. so I need you
to keep an open mind.

485
00:29:25.432 --> 00:29:27.850
- [breathes deeply]
- About what?

486
00:29:27.851 --> 00:29:31.313
I found an address for Davide.

487
00:29:32.940 --> 00:29:35.775
- No.
- Aren't you sick of them

488
00:29:35.776 --> 00:29:38.945
thinking that we don't deserve answers
because we're just her friends?

489
00:29:38.946 --> 00:29:40.863
- Of course. I am.
- He painted her.

490
00:29:40.864 --> 00:29:42.490
He-He partied with her.

491
00:29:42.491 --> 00:29:45.117
He may know something about what happened.

492
00:29:45.118 --> 00:29:47.245
We can't just interfere
with the investigation.

493
00:29:47.246 --> 00:29:50.832
Ah. [sighing]

494
00:29:51.667 --> 00:29:53.085
She doesn't talk back.

495
00:29:54.253 --> 00:29:55.546
Who?

496
00:29:56.421 --> 00:30:00.259
There's this grief counselor on YouTube.

497
00:30:02.010 --> 00:30:06.515
and she suggests that you talk
to your deceased loved ones.

498
00:30:07.474 --> 00:30:08.975
So I've been trying that.

499
00:30:08.976 --> 00:30:12.186
You know. when people
aren't in the house or asleep.

500
00:30:12.187 --> 00:30:14.022
so they don't think I'm crazy. [chuckles]

501
00:30:15.607 --> 00:30:17.358
And I just talk to her.

502
00:30:17.359 --> 00:30:21.320
I tell her. you know.
how Artie just lost another tooth.

503
00:30:21.321 --> 00:30:24.658
and how Howard may have a lead
on a new job. and…

504
00:30:27.452 --> 00:30:28.620
But she doesn't answer.

505
00:30:34.042 --> 00:30:35.377
She doesn't talk back.

506
00:30:39.256 --> 00:30:41.091
And I have so many questions.

507
00:30:43.177 --> 00:30:44.178
Please help.

508
00:30:53.770 --> 00:30:55.938
[sighs] Hello.

509
00:30:55.939 --> 00:30:57.815
[Davide] Leave me the hell alone.

510
00:30:57.816 --> 00:31:01.569
[stammers] Sir. we're not reporters.
we're not police officers.

511
00:31:01.570 --> 00:31:03.613
We're friends of Nancy's.

512
00:31:03.614 --> 00:31:05.032
We just want to talk.

513
00:31:06.074 --> 00:31:07.575
[Davide] Go away.

514
00:31:07.576 --> 00:31:08.701
[Mary] No.

515
00:31:08.702 --> 00:31:10.871
We will not go away.

516
00:31:11.788 --> 00:31:14.333
- Let us in. Please.
- Mary.

517
00:31:15.000 --> 00:31:16.792
Are you out of your fucking mind?

518
00:31:16.793 --> 00:31:19.587
Please. She was our friend.

519
00:31:19.588 --> 00:31:21.339
[panting]

520
00:31:21.340 --> 00:31:22.341
Please.

521
00:31:54.581 --> 00:31:58.126
[Davide] She saw my work at a collector's
and reached out.

522
00:31:58.710 --> 00:32:02.380
I thought she was one of those white women
who. no offense.

523
00:32:02.381 --> 00:32:06.259
wanted me to paint what they think
is their true authentic self.

524
00:32:06.260 --> 00:32:07.553
But after a few sketches.

525
00:32:08.720 --> 00:32:10.721
it was clear
that she was someone different.

526
00:32:10.722 --> 00:32:13.057
She wanted me to paint her scars.

527
00:32:13.058 --> 00:32:15.601
She said they were
from an accident that she caused.

528
00:32:15.602 --> 00:32:18.229
She said the scars were her fault?

529
00:32:18.230 --> 00:32:20.106
They most definitely were not her fault.

530
00:32:20.107 --> 00:32:25.111
Davide. from the photo. it seemed
like you two knew each other so well.

531
00:32:25.112 --> 00:32:28.197
I don't even remember that picture.

532
00:32:28.198 --> 00:32:29.949
She was barely at the party.

533
00:32:29.950 --> 00:32:31.325
I think the guy she brought

534
00:32:31.326 --> 00:32:33.077
- wasn't having a good time.
- What?

535
00:32:33.078 --> 00:32:34.745
[Mary] What do you mean
the guy that she brought?

536
00:32:34.746 --> 00:32:36.832
Davide. do you remember
what he looked like?

537
00:32:37.916 --> 00:32:38.917
He was white.

538
00:32:39.751 --> 00:32:41.544
Do you think she could've been
with Robert?

539
00:32:41.545 --> 00:32:43.964
No. No. he had never seen that photo.

540
00:32:45.883 --> 00:32:46.966
Can you look at this…

541
00:32:46.967 --> 00:32:49.051
- He would've told me.
- Hold on.

542
00:32:49.052 --> 00:32:50.720
Can you look at this photo for me?

543
00:32:50.721 --> 00:32:52.597
Do you recognize this man?

544
00:32:52.598 --> 00:32:55.391
[Davide] If I remembered anything
more than his race. I would've said so.

545
00:32:55.392 --> 00:32:57.101
I told the police. It's on them.

546
00:32:57.102 --> 00:32:59.770
- You barely looked at the photo.
- No. you've asked your last question.

547
00:32:59.771 --> 00:33:01.689
This… [speaks Xhosa]

548
00:33:01.690 --> 00:33:03.901
[in English]
I was put in jail. And for what?

549
00:33:04.651 --> 00:33:06.569
I did nothing. Nothing.

550
00:33:06.570 --> 00:33:09.489
Okay. We've taken enough of your time.

551
00:33:10.741 --> 00:33:12.034
Thank you.

552
00:33:15.412 --> 00:33:16.580
Where were you?

553
00:33:17.456 --> 00:33:18.582
Excuse me?

554
00:33:19.374 --> 00:33:21.460
Your best friend was in a death spiral.

555
00:33:22.252 --> 00:33:24.337
She was drowning in her own misery.

556
00:33:24.338 --> 00:33:25.672
That's what I saw.

557
00:33:26.256 --> 00:33:27.673
That's what I painted.

558
00:33:27.674 --> 00:33:30.259
So. where were you
when she needed you the most?

559
00:33:30.260 --> 00:33:31.594
She wasn't hiding it.

560
00:33:31.595 --> 00:33:35.098
If you didn't see it.
it's because you didn't want to.

561
00:33:36.600 --> 00:33:38.769
Come on. Come on. let's go.

562
00:33:42.397 --> 00:33:45.399
I'd like the centerpieces
to be a bit more consistent.

563
00:33:45.400 --> 00:33:48.486
And I'd like three people at every corner.
I don't want a bottleneck.

564
00:33:48.487 --> 00:33:50.780
- No. The entire time. Okay? Thank you.
- [Kit] …your fault.

565
00:33:50.781 --> 00:33:52.073
Your fault.

566
00:33:52.074 --> 00:33:53.908
- [Robert] She did not--
- You did not.

567
00:33:53.909 --> 00:33:55.160
I told you over and…

568
00:34:04.294 --> 00:34:06.129
Hey. Everything okay?

569
00:34:06.672 --> 00:34:08.381
[Robert] Despite my strong objection.

570
00:34:08.382 --> 00:34:11.717
my family went ahead and hired that
crisis PR firm to pressure the police.

571
00:34:12.469 --> 00:34:14.179
They're the ones who leaked that photo.

572
00:34:14.763 --> 00:34:16.014
Can you fucking believe it?

573
00:34:16.889 --> 00:34:19.476
They're the reason Davide Boyette
was arrested. My family.

574
00:34:20.101 --> 00:34:21.477
That's disgusting.

575
00:34:21.478 --> 00:34:24.147
They thought it would
help keep the press off of us.

576
00:34:24.773 --> 00:34:26.189
Apparently. who gives a fuck

577
00:34:26.190 --> 00:34:29.069
if an innocent man has to sit
behind bars for weeks?

578
00:34:30.362 --> 00:34:34.615
And you've never met him. right?

579
00:34:34.616 --> 00:34:36.408
[stammers] Never met who?

580
00:34:36.409 --> 00:34:37.411
Davide.

581
00:34:38.203 --> 00:34:40.289
I mean. the first time you saw him
was on the news.

582
00:34:40.998 --> 00:34:43.541
Eleanor. you were here.
We saw him together.

583
00:34:43.542 --> 00:34:44.709
What are you getting at?

584
00:34:44.710 --> 00:34:47.295
I'm… No. I'm not getting at anything. I…

585
00:34:49.047 --> 00:34:52.841
I just know what it means
to be from a powerful family.

586
00:34:52.842 --> 00:34:56.428
Sometimes you can't see
how they're pulling the strings.

587
00:34:56.429 --> 00:35:01.143
Well. you managed
to make your own way in the world.

588
00:35:01.852 --> 00:35:03.520
- You think?
- Yeah.

589
00:35:04.146 --> 00:35:08.567
I constantly feel them
looking over my shoulder.

590
00:35:10.444 --> 00:35:12.529
Yeah. but you do the things
that matter to you.

591
00:35:15.073 --> 00:35:17.075
I-I admire that.

592
00:35:17.576 --> 00:35:18.952
Always have.

593
00:35:20.287 --> 00:35:21.288
[Cora] Dad?

594
00:35:22.206 --> 00:35:23.207
Dad!

595
00:35:26.919 --> 00:35:28.836
- Hey.
- Why are Mom's things boxed up?

596
00:35:28.837 --> 00:35:30.963
Uh. I was… I was just organizing.

597
00:35:30.964 --> 00:35:33.299
[Cora stammers]
You-You can't get rid of them.

598
00:35:33.300 --> 00:35:35.051
[Robert] Cora. that's not what this is.

599
00:35:35.052 --> 00:35:36.344
You have to understand.

600
00:35:36.345 --> 00:35:38.930
it's very difficult for me
to have her things all around…

601
00:35:38.931 --> 00:35:41.015
So. what? You're just gonna erase her?

602
00:35:41.016 --> 00:35:42.350
[sighs]

603
00:35:42.351 --> 00:35:44.810
No. No. he can't do that.

604
00:35:44.811 --> 00:35:46.354
That's impossible. Cora.

605
00:35:46.355 --> 00:35:48.105
This is all I have!

606
00:35:48.106 --> 00:35:51.400
What's in these boxes
is all I have of left of my mom.

607
00:35:51.401 --> 00:35:52.735
I understand. sweetie. I…

608
00:35:52.736 --> 00:35:54.696
Oh. Cora. Come here.

609
00:35:58.867 --> 00:36:00.285
[sighs]

610
00:36:02.955 --> 00:36:06.959
You know my car belonged to my dad
before he passed?

611
00:36:08.335 --> 00:36:12.339
And he gave me this necklace.

612
00:36:13.757 --> 00:36:17.844
And I even have a fishing rod of his
hanging on the wall in my apartment

613
00:36:17.845 --> 00:36:20.179
because I want to feel his presence.

614
00:36:20.180 --> 00:36:22.766
So I keep all of those things
really close to me.

615
00:36:24.434 --> 00:36:25.602
So you can do that.

616
00:36:26.436 --> 00:36:29.272
You can look at all this stuff and just.

617
00:36:29.273 --> 00:36:33.110
whatever reminds you of her.
you take that. You keep it close to you.

618
00:36:34.444 --> 00:36:35.945
And the rest of it.

619
00:36:35.946 --> 00:36:38.949
we will make sure
to put somewhere very special.

620
00:36:39.491 --> 00:36:42.744
Like. maybe the Ojai house.

621
00:36:43.912 --> 00:36:47.249
That way you can go there
whenever you want to feel her presence.

622
00:36:48.458 --> 00:36:50.335
Okay. [sniffles]

623
00:36:51.712 --> 00:36:53.796
You don't have to let go of your mom.

624
00:36:53.797 --> 00:36:56.633
Your dad would never ask you to do that.

625
00:37:00.220 --> 00:37:01.221
[Cora sniffles]

626
00:37:06.602 --> 00:37:08.519
- [sniffling]
- Oh. sweetie.

627
00:37:08.520 --> 00:37:09.855
[Cora cries]

628
00:37:11.982 --> 00:37:13.066
Hey. thanks.

629
00:37:18.739 --> 00:37:21.742
[sighs] I don't blame her
for calling it off.

630
00:37:22.451 --> 00:37:24.870
She'll probably have more fun
back at school anyway.

631
00:37:27.289 --> 00:37:29.123
I really fucked up this birthday.

632
00:37:29.124 --> 00:37:32.084
I'm the one who insisted
that you throw her a party.

633
00:37:32.085 --> 00:37:34.129
Y-You've done nothing but help.

634
00:37:34.713 --> 00:37:36.465
I think Cora just needs some time.

635
00:37:37.633 --> 00:37:39.050
It's so unnatural. you know?

636
00:37:39.051 --> 00:37:41.178
Nobody prepares a kid to lose a parent.

637
00:37:41.720 --> 00:37:43.889
No one prepared us. [chuckles]

638
00:37:46.141 --> 00:37:49.561
You know. part of me was relieved
when the police came and took her things.

639
00:37:50.395 --> 00:37:54.106
I don't want to erase her.
but everywhere I look

640
00:37:54.107 --> 00:37:58.819
is something of hers just shouting at me
about this secret life that she had.

641
00:37:58.820 --> 00:38:00.948
A fucking affair that she kept from me.

642
00:38:02.783 --> 00:38:05.619
It's deafening. It's all around.

643
00:38:09.498 --> 00:38:13.252
Well. I think that the Ojai house is gonna
be the perfect place for all this stuff.

644
00:38:14.002 --> 00:38:15.003
[Robert] Yeah.

645
00:38:15.629 --> 00:38:18.048
[sighs] It's gonna be hard
to go out there alone.

646
00:38:21.343 --> 00:38:23.554
["With Or Without You" playing]

647
00:38:57.963 --> 00:38:59.131
[birds chirping]

648
00:39:07.472 --> 00:39:09.474
[music continues]

649
00:39:35.959 --> 00:39:36.960
[music fades. ends]

650
00:39:42.174 --> 00:39:43.175
[chuckles]

651
00:39:50.599 --> 00:39:51.600
[sighs]

652
00:39:53.227 --> 00:39:54.228
[chuckles]

653
00:39:56.980 --> 00:39:59.399
[chuckling]

654
00:40:05.322 --> 00:40:06.822
She used that on every person

655
00:40:06.823 --> 00:40:08.157
- in my family.
- Mm-hmm.

656
00:40:08.158 --> 00:40:10.326
- Everyone hated it.
- [chuckles]

657
00:40:10.327 --> 00:40:11.994
And nothing made her laugh harder.

658
00:40:11.995 --> 00:40:14.997
Every time she used it.
she would laugh for hours.

659
00:40:14.998 --> 00:40:16.834
[chuckles]

660
00:40:18.043 --> 00:40:19.126
[exclaims]

661
00:40:19.127 --> 00:40:20.963
[chuckling]

662
00:40:21.588 --> 00:40:24.007
- [chuckles] That's funny.
- [laughing]

663
00:40:33.976 --> 00:40:36.477
I didn't know how much pain she was in.

664
00:40:36.478 --> 00:40:37.937
[cries]

665
00:40:37.938 --> 00:40:43.150
How could I have not seen
what she was going through?

666
00:40:43.151 --> 00:40:44.820
[sighs] Hey. none of us did.

667
00:40:46.196 --> 00:40:47.447
I missed it.

668
00:40:48.198 --> 00:40:50.200
I just… I just missed it.

669
00:40:50.909 --> 00:40:54.161
- [cries]
- Hey. it's okay. So did I.

670
00:40:54.162 --> 00:40:56.164
Oh. God. [cries]

671
00:41:03.630 --> 00:41:05.632
[crying]

672
00:41:14.766 --> 00:41:15.975
[breathes shakily]

673
00:41:15.976 --> 00:41:17.978
[gentle music playing]

674
00:41:42.544 --> 00:41:43.545
[sighs]

675
00:41:59.561 --> 00:42:01.563
[breathing deeply]

676
00:42:02.814 --> 00:42:04.733
[Eleanor moaning]

677
00:42:23.126 --> 00:42:24.127
[pants]

678
00:42:31.510 --> 00:42:33.846
[both panting. moaning]

679
00:42:51.822 --> 00:42:53.240
[moans. pants]

680
00:43:08.297 --> 00:43:09.798
[Eleanor moaning]

681
00:43:12.092 --> 00:43:15.095
[both panting. moaning]

682
00:43:17.181 --> 00:43:19.016
[Eleanor sighs. moans]

683
00:43:23.187 --> 00:43:25.189
[crickets chirping]

684
00:43:57.804 --> 00:43:59.556
[sighs]

685
00:44:06.396 --> 00:44:09.441
[Eleanor]
<i>She asked me once if I liked Robert.</i>

686
00:44:14.404 --> 00:44:16.823
<i>I remember how quickly I said no.</i>

687
00:44:22.412 --> 00:44:27.084
<i>She must have known I was lying.
How could she not?</i>

688
00:44:31.922 --> 00:44:36.802
<i>I was never as good as she was
at pretending.</i>

689
00:44:37.761 --> 00:44:40.429
<i>At creating my own reality.</i>

690
00:44:40.430 --> 00:44:41.431
[sighs]

691
00:44:43.308 --> 00:44:45.894
<i>So maybe this is my chance.</i>

692
00:44:47.521 --> 00:44:49.398
<i>And maybe she would understand.</i>

693
00:44:50.190 --> 00:44:53.109
<i>Because she was lying too.</i>

694
00:44:53.110 --> 00:44:55.069
<i>Lying to Robert.</i>

695
00:44:55.070 --> 00:44:56.446
<i>Lying to all of us.</i>

696
00:45:07.082 --> 00:45:11.086
[Robert] <i>Nancy.
I need to start with an apology.</i>

697
00:45:11.837 --> 00:45:14.256
<i>My reaction was extreme.</i>

698
00:45:15.424 --> 00:45:19.928
<i>I was horrible to you
and I'm sorry I scared you so badly.</i>

699
00:45:20.470 --> 00:45:22.889
<i>But you can hardly
blame me for being angry</i>

700
00:45:22.890 --> 00:45:24.724
<i>when you're sleeping with someone else.</i>

701
00:45:24.725 --> 00:45:26.727
[tense music playing]

702
00:45:28.145 --> 00:45:30.981
Hey. You okay?

703
00:45:36.528 --> 00:45:38.530
["Secrets" playing]

704
